<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Acting Secretary of State to
                        the Embassy in Chile</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1949v01</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d322</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">322</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1949-11-14T18:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1949-11-14T18:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-11-14T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-11-14T18:00:00-05:00" n="322" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d322">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.014 Antarctic/11–1449: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Embassy in Chile</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-11-14T18:00:00-05:00">November 14, 1949—6 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>376. Chil and UK <gloss target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss>s confirm that exchange of
                    notes renewing tripartite understanding of Jan 18 will take place Nov 18 (<gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 297, Sep 8.<note n="1" xml:id="d322fn1">Not printed, but see footnote 2 to telegram 3729, September 16, from
                        London, <ref target="#pg_809">p. 809</ref>.</note>). Text of notes identical
                    with previous text except for omission word “routine”. Dept will issue press
                    release similar release Jan 18 upon <gloss target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss> Santiago
                    confirmation exchange notes has taken place<note n="2" xml:id="d322fn2">For the
                        text of the statement issued to the press on November 19, see Department of
                        State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, November 28, 1949, p. 833. Regarding
                        the Department’s statement to the press of January 18, see the editorial
                        note, <ref target="#pg_793">p. 793</ref>
                    </note> Chil desires our press release be issued same day.</p>
                <p>To Santiago as 376; London as 4101; BAires as 685.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Webb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
